<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>JavaScript Demonstration</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f9;
            color: #333;
        }
        .container {
            background: #fff;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        h1 { color: #2c3e50; }
        .welcome-msg {
            font-size: 1.2em;
            color: #27ae60;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        .info-box {
            background: #e8f4fd;
            border-left: 5px solid #3498db;
            padding: 15px;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #3498db;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 16px;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #2980b9;
        }
    </style>
    <!-- Internal JavaScript -->
    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            console.log("--- Internal JS: DOM Content Loaded ---");
            
            const welcomeDiv = document.getElementById('welcome');
            welcomeDiv.textContent = "Welcome! This page demonstrates various JavaScript implementations.";
            
            // Demonstrate console.error()
            if (!window.navigator) {
                console.error("Critical Error: Navigator object not found!");
            } else {
                console.log("Internal JS: Navigator object verified.");
            }
        });

        function triggerError() {
            console.error("This is a simulated error message using console.error().");
        }
    </script>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>JavaScript Implementation Demo</h1>
        <p>This page uses three types of JavaScript:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Inline:</strong> Used in the button's <code>onclick</code> attribute.</li>
            <li><strong>Internal:</strong> Located in the <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag in the head.</li>
            <li><strong>External:</strong> Loaded from <code>script.js</code>.</li>
        </ul>

        <div id="welcome" class="welcome-msg"></div>

        <div class="info-box">
            <p>Check the <strong>Browser Console</strong> (F12) to see the logs from <code>console.log()</code>, <code>console.table()</code>, <code>console.trace()</code>, and <code>console.error()</code>.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
            <!-- Inline JavaScript -->
            <button onclick="alert('Hello! This is an inline JavaScript alert.'); triggerError();">
                Click for Inline JS & Error Log
            </button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- External JavaScript -->
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
